r Aslam Baloch killed in Kandahar bombings, say sources|accessdate=26 December 2018|newspaper=Business Standard}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Iraq|1963}} {{small|(1948\u201370)}}<ref name=h>{{cite news\n | title = Iraq's shadow on Balochistan\n | author = B Raman\n | newspaper = Asia Times\n | url = http://www.atimes.com/atimes/South_Asia/EA25Df01.html\n | date = 25 January 2003}}</ref>\n*{{Flag|Republic of Afghanistan}} {{small|(until 1978)}}<ref>{{cite book|title=Dynamics of Political Development in Afghanistan: The British, Russian, and American Invasions|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=0UzJAAAAQBAJ&dq|date=18 October 2010|last=Emadi|first=H.|pages=94\u201395|publisher=Springer}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|title=Pakistan's Inter-Services Intelligence Directorate: Covert Action and Internal Operations|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=SzGTDAAAQBAJ&dq|date=1 July 2016|publisher=Routledge|last=Sirrs|first=Owen L.}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|title=Faith, Unity, Discipline: The Inter-Service-Intelligence (ISI) of Pakistan|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=y_cgDgAAQBAJ&dq|date=15 November 2016|publisher=Oxford University Press|last=Kiessling|first=Hein}}</ref>\n----\n'''Sectarian groups'''\n*[[Jundallah (Iran)|Jundallah]] {{small|(2003\u201312)}}<ref>{{cite web\n   | title = Iran Offers Short-Term  Solutions To Long-Term  Problems Of Baluch Minority\n   | last = Aryan | first = Hossein\n   | publisher = Radio Free Europe/Radio Liberty\n   | url = http://www.rferl.org/content/Iran_Offers_ShortTerm_Solutions_To_LongTerm_Problems_Of_Baluch_Minority/1858243.html\n   | date = 22 October 2009\n }}</ref><ref>{{cite news\n   | title = Iranian group makes kidnap claim \u2013 Middle East\n   | publisher = Al Jazeera\n   | url = http://english.aljazeera.net/video/middleeast/2010/10/2010101016024116222.html\n   | date = 10 October 2010\n }}</ref>\n*{{flagicon image|Flag of Jaish al-Adl.svg}} [[Jaish ul-Adl]] {{small|(since 2012)}}\n*{{flagicon image|AQMI Flag asymmetric.svg}} [[Jundallah 