file Of A Sunni Extremist Group\n   | author = Abubakar Siddique\n   | publisher = Radio Free Europe/Radio Liberty\n   | url = http://www.rferl.org/content/Jundallah_Profile_Of_A_Sunni_Extremist_Group/1856699.html\n   | date = 20 October 2009\n }}</ref>\n* [[Islamic Revolutionary Guard Corps|IRGC]] {{small|(since 1980)}}\n* [[Islamic Republic of Iran Border Guard Command|Border Guard]] {{small|(since 2000)}}\n{{flagicon|Iran|1964}} [[Imperial State of Iran]] {{small|(until 1979)}}<ref>{{cite news\n   | title = Jundallah: Profile Of A Sunni Extremist Group\n   | author = Abubakar Siddique\n   | publisher = Radio Free Europe/Radio Liberty\n   | url = http://www.rferl.org/content/Jundallah_Profile_Of_A_Sunni_Extremist_Group/1856699.html\n   | date = 20 October 2009\n }}</ref>\n* [[Military history of Iran#Pahlavi Era (1925 to 1979)|Imperial Iranian Army]]\n| combatant2        = '''[[Baloch nationalism|Baloch separatist groups]]'''\n* {{flagicon image|Balochistan Flag.png}} [[Baloch Republican Army|BRA]]\n* [[Baluch Liberation Front|BLF]]\n* [[United Baloch Army|UBA]]\n* [[Lashkar-e-Balochistan|LeB]]\n* [[Balochistan Liberation United Front|BLUF]]\n* [[Baloch Students Organization|BSO (Azad)]]\n'''Baloch terrorist groups'''\n* {{flagicon image|Balochistan Flag.png}} [[Balochistan Liberation Army|BLA]]<ref name=\"USA\">{{cite web|url=https://www.state.gov/terrorist-designations-of-balochistan-liberation-army-and-husain-ali-hazzima-and-amendments-to-the-terrorist-designations-of-jundallah/|title=Terrorist Designations of Balochistan Liberation Army and Husain Ali Hazzima and Amendments to the Terrorist Designations of Jundallah|date=2 July 2019|work=U.S. Department of State}}</ref>\n'''Supported by:'''{{plainlist|\n*{{flag|India}} <ref name=\"AP\">{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=6WhNDwAAQBAJ&hl=ar&source=gbs_navlinks_s|title=My Enemy's Enemy: India in Afghanistan from the Soviet Invasion to US Withdrawal|year=2017|publisher=Oxford University Press|last=Paliwal|first=Avinash|pages=38, 240 and 241}}</ref>\n*{{Flag|Afghanistan}}<ref name=\"New York Times13\">{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/12/27/world/asia/pakistan-baluch-afghanistan-bombing.html|title=Suicide Bombing Kills Pakistani Insurgent Wanted for Attack on Chinese|accessdate=27 December 2018|newspaper=New York Times|quote=Afghan officials confirmed that General Raziq had housed Baluch separatist leaders in Kandahar for years.}}</ref><ref name=\"Tolo News13\">{{cite news|url=https://www.tolonews.com/afghanistan/baloch-separatist-leader-killed-kandahar-attack-reports|title=Baloch Separatist Leader Killed In Kandahar Attack: Reports|accessdate=26 December 2018|quote=The Baloch separatist Aslam Baloch was living in Afghanistan\u2019s Kandahar province since 2005|publisher=Tolo news}}</ref><ref name=\"Business Standard13\">{{cite news|url=https://wap.business-standard.com/article/news-ani/bla-commander-aslam-baloch-killed-in-kandahar-bombings-say-sources-118122600987_1.html|title=BLA commander Aslam Baloch killed in Kandahar bombings, say sources|accessdate=26 December 2018|newspaper=Business Standard}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Iraq|1963}} {{small|(1948\u201370)}}<ref name=h>{{cite news\n | title = Iraq's shadow on Balochistan\n | author = B Raman\n | newspaper = Asia Times\n | url = http://www.atimes.com/atimes/South_Asia/EA25Df01.html\n | date = 25 January 2003}}</ref>\n*{{Flag|Republic of Afghanistan}} {{small|(until 1978)}}<ref>{{cite book|title=Dynamics of Political Development in Afghanistan: The British, Russian, and American Invasions|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=0UzJAAAAQBAJ&dq|date=18 October 2010|last=Emadi|first=H.|pages=94\u201395|publisher=Springer}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|title=Pakistan's Inter-Services Intelligence Directorate: Covert Action and Internal Operations|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=SzGTDAAAQBAJ&dq|date=1 July 2016|publisher=Routledge|last=Sirrs|first=Owen L.}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|title=Faith, Unity, Discipline: The Inter-Service-Intelligence (ISI) of Pakistan|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=y_cgDgAAQBAJ&dq|date=15 November 2016|publisher=Oxford University Press|last=Kiessling|first=Hein}}</ref>\n----\n'''Sectarian groups'''\n*[[Jundallah (Iran)|Jundallah]] {{small|(2003\u201312)}}<ref>{{cite web\n   | title = Iran Offers Short-Term  Solutions To Long-Term  Problems Of Baluch Minority\n   | last = Aryan | first = Hossein\n   | publisher = Radio Free Europe/Radio Liberty\n   | url = http://www.rferl.org/content/Iran_Offers_ShortTerm_Solutions_To_LongTerm_Problems_Of_Baluch_Minority/1858243.html\n   | date = 22 October 2009\n }}</ref><ref>{{cite news\n   | title = Iranian group makes kidnap claim \u2013 Middle East\n   | publisher = Al Jazeera\n   | url = http://english.aljazeera.net/video/middleeast/2010/10/2010101016024116222.html\n   | date = 10 October 2010\n }}</ref>\n*{{flagicon image|Flag of Jaish al-Adl.svg}} [[Jaish ul-Adl]] {{small|(since 2012)}}\n*{{flagicon image|AQMI Flag asymmetric.svg}} [[Jundallah (Pakistan)|Jundallah]] {{small|(since 1996)}}\n*{{flagicon image|Flag of Jihad.svg}} [[Al-Qaeda]] {{small|(since 1988)}}\n*{{flagicon image|Flag of Jihad.svg}} [[Lashkar-e-Jhangvi]] {{small|(since 1996)}}<ref name=h/>\n*{{flagicon image|Flag of Jihad.svg}} [[Sipah-e-Sahaba Pakistan|Sipah-e-Sahaba]] {{small|(since 1985)}}<ref name=h/>}}\n| commander1        = {{plainlist|\n*[[File:Flag of the President of Pakistan.svg|25px]] '''[[Arif Alvi]]'''<br />(2018\u2013present)\n*[[File:Flag of the President of Pakistan.svg|25px]] [[Mamnoon Hussain]]<br />(2013\u201318)\n*[[File:Flag of the President of Pakistan.svg|25px]] [[Asif Ali Zardari]]<br />(2008\u201313)\n*[[File:Flag of the President of Pakistan.svg|25px]] [[Pervez Musharraf]]<br />(2001\u201308)\n*[[File:Flag of the President of Pakistan.svg|25px]] [[Muhammad Rafiq Tarar]]<br />(1998\u201301)\n*[[File:Flag of the President of Pakistan.svg|25px]] [[Farooq Leghari]]<br />(1993\u201397)\n*[[File:Flag of the President